Path: godot/classes/class_editorspinslider.rst
Summary: Introduces the EditorSpinSlider, a control for editing numeric values in the Godot editor, inheriting from Range, Control, CanvasItem, Node, and Object.
---CHUNK---
Document: EditorSpinSlider
Path: godot/classes/class_editorspinslider.rst
Summary: Describes the EditorSpinSlider control node used in the Godot editor for editing numeric values.
Inherits: Range < CanvasItem < Node < Object
This Control node is used in the editor's Inspector dock to allow editing of numeric values. Can be used with EditorInspectorPlugin to recreate the same behavior.

If the Range.step value is 1, the EditorSpinSlider will display up/down arrows, similar to SpinBox. If the Range.step value is not 1, a slider will be displayed instead.
---CHUNK---
Document: EditorSpinSlider
Path: godot/classes/class_editorspinslider.rst
Summary: Defines the properties available for the EditorSpinSlider class.

Properties
- control_state (ControlState): The current control state of the spin slider. Default: 0.
- deferred_drag_mode (bool): If true, the drag operation will only start after a small delay. Default: false.
- editing_integer (bool): If true, the spin slider will only accept integer values. Default: false.
- flat (bool): If true, the spin slider will have a flat appearance. Default: false.
- focus_mode (FocusMode): Overrides the focus mode inherited from Control. Default: 2.
- hide_slider (bool): If true, the slider part of the spin slider will be hidden. Default: false.
- label (String): The text label displayed next to the spin slider. Default: "".
- read_only (bool): If true, the spin slider cannot be edited. Default: false.
- size_flags_vertical (bitfield[SizeFlags]): Overrides the vertical size flags inherited from Control. Default: 1.
- step (float): Overrides the step value inherited from Range. Default: 1.0.
- suffix (String): The suffix displayed after the value. Default: "".
---CHUNK---
Document: EditorSpinSlider
Path: godot/classes/class_editorspinslider.rst
Summary: Defines theme properties for the EditorSpinSlider class.

Theme Properties:
* updown (Texture2D): The icon for the up/down arrows.
* updown_disabled (Texture2D): The icon for the disabled up/down arrows.
