Document: EditorSpinSlider
Path: godot/classes/class_editorspinslider.rst
Summary: This section describes the signals and enumerations available for the EditorSpinSlider class in Godot Engine.

Signals
grabbed()
Emitted when the spinner/slider is grabbed.
ungrabbed()
Emitted when the spinner/slider is ungrabbed.
updown_pressed()
Emitted when the updown button is pressed.
value_focus_entered()
Emitted when the value form gains focus.
value_focus_exited()
Emitted when the value form loses focus.

Enumerations
enum ControlState:
CONTROL_STATE_DEFAULT = 0
The type of control used will depend on the value of editing_integer. Up-down arrows if true, a slider if false.
CONTROL_STATE_PREFER_SLIDER = 1
A slider will always be used, even if editing_integer is enabled.
CONTROL_STATE_HIDE = 2
Neither the up-down arrows nor the slider will be shown.
---CHUNK---
Document: EditorSpinSlider
Path: godot/classes/class_editorspinslider.rst
Summary: Describes the properties and member variables of the EditorSpinSlider class in Godot Engine.

Property: control_state (ControlState)
Description: The state in which the control used to manipulate the value will be.
Default: 0
Setter: set_control_state
Getter: get_control_state

Property: deferred_drag_mode (bool)
Description: If true, changing via dragging is applied only at the end of the input (for example, when the user releases a mouse button).
Default: false
Setter: set_deferred_drag_mode_enabled
Getter: is_deferred_drag_mode_enabled

Property: editing_integer (bool)
Description: If true, the EditorSpinSlider is considered to be editing an integer value. If false, the EditorSpinSlider is considered to be editing a floating-point value. This is used to determine whether a slider should be drawn by default. The slider is only drawn for floats; integers use up-down arrows similar to SpinBox instead, unless control_state is set to CONTROL_STATE_PREFER_SLIDER. It will also use EditorSettings.interface/inspector/integer_drag_speed instead of EditorSettings.interface/inspector/float_drag_speed if the slider is available.
Default: false
Setter: set_editing_integer
Getter: is_editing_integer

Property: flat (bool)
Description: If true, the slider will not draw background.
Default: false
Setter: set_flat
Getter: is_flat

Property: hide_slider (bool)
Description: Deprecated: Use control_state instead. If true, the slider and up/down arrows are hidden.
Default: false
Setter: set_hide_slider
Getter: is_hiding_slider

Property: label (String)
Description: The text that displays to the left of the value.
Default: ""
Setter: set_label
Getter: get_label

Property: read_only (bool)
Description: If true, the slider can't be interacted with.
Default: false
Setter: set_read_only
Getter: is_read_only

Property: suffix (String)
Description: The suffix to display after the value (in a faded color). This should generally be a plural word. You may have to use an abbreviation if the suffix is too long to be displayed.
Default: ""
Setter: set_suffix
Getter: get_suffix
